{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:3.0.0`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6970-fails-javac-compile-org.neo4j.bolt-neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled-3.0.0-cd9b3292\n\nThe first failing stage was `:compileTestJava`: `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-35-23-795015Z.log` shows 28 compilation errors in `Neo4j_bolt_connection_pooledTest.java` because the test still targeted the 2.0.0 `BoltConnection` API. Missing/changed symbols include `onLoop`, `run`, `pull`, `telemetry`, `route`, `beginTransaction`, `runInAutoCommitTransaction`, `discard`, `commit`, `rollback`, `clear`, and `FakeBoltConnection` also no longer matched the interface (`write(List<Message>)`).\n\nAutomation then made progress, but `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-39-22-002069Z.log` still had 2 JVM test assertion failures caused by swapped argument order in `pull` and `discard`. After that, the reruns in `human-intervention-logs/org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:3.0.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-39-45-510648Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-40-52-735899Z.log`, and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-18T13-41-14-005551Z.log` all show `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, including 10/10 native tests passing. That makes the most likely remaining failure an automation/metrics handoff problem rather than a still-failing library test. `stats/org.neo4j.bolt/neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled/3.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `iterations: 2`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`, even though the preserved branch contains a passing candidate commit.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Inspect the preserved branch and the passing candidate commit on it to confirm the test/API adaptation is acceptable.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.neo4j.bolt:neo4j-bolt-connection-pooled:3.0.0` from that branch to verify the preserved candidate is still green.\n3. If it passes, open a manual PR or cherry-pick the candidate; if it does not, investigate why metrics/reporting marked the run failed despite the successful Gradle logs."}}
